1
00:00:05,260 --> 00:00:06,380
(Food break unlocked!)

2
00:00:06,380 --> 00:00:07,940
(Coming up)

3
00:00:07,960 --> 00:00:09,400
(Lotus Root & Pork Rib Soup)
Is that bone broth?

4
00:00:09,400 --> 00:00:10,040
Where are the drinks?

5
00:00:10,040 --> 00:00:11,600
(Jin to the rescue)
What do you want?

6
00:00:11,600 --> 00:00:12,840
Thai tea, orange juice, or coffee?

7
00:00:12,840 --> 00:00:15,160
(Someone's hungry)
Jin, can you top mine off?

8
00:00:15,160 --> 00:00:16,280
Have some veggies.

9
00:00:16,280 --> 00:00:17,280
(Dig in)
Let's eat.

10
00:00:17,280 --> 00:00:18,320
(Help yourself)
Serve yourself.

11
00:00:25,280 --> 00:00:27,160
My legendary kick...

12
00:00:27,160 --> 00:00:29,600
But your legendary kick
actually paid off later.

13
00:00:29,600 --> 00:00:30,720
That was on purpose.

14
00:00:30,720 --> 00:00:31,680
I really didn't want to do the splits,

15
00:00:31,680 --> 00:00:33,720
but I had to commit to the character.

16
00:00:33,720 --> 00:00:35,920
You're crazy flexible, though.

17
00:00:35,920 --> 00:00:38,400
I trained in martial arts
as a kid for a while.

18
00:00:38,400 --> 00:00:39,520
I got three.

19
00:00:41,360 --> 00:00:42,880
(Suddenly serious)
You got three today?

20
00:00:42,880 --> 00:00:43,880
Scan what?

21
00:00:43,880 --> 00:00:44,840
Got points? You eat.

22
00:00:44,840 --> 00:00:46,000
If you don't,

23
00:00:46,000 --> 00:00:47,760
you ask someone else to buy you food.

24
00:00:47,760 --> 00:00:48,960
So just ask? Easy.

25
00:00:48,960 --> 00:00:50,200
(Zero hesitation)
Please.

26
00:00:50,200 --> 00:00:51,080
Feed me.

27
00:00:51,080 --> 00:00:53,520
I'm hungry. Please, feed me.

28
00:00:54,520 --> 00:00:56,040
What'd you guys do in France?

29
00:00:56,040 --> 00:00:56,760
She loved it.

30
00:00:56,760 --> 00:00:57,400
Just sitting in the car.

31
00:00:57,400 --> 00:00:58,000
We were driving around,

32
00:00:58,000 --> 00:01:00,280
and she kept saying
everywhere looked like a photo op.

33
00:01:00,280 --> 00:01:01,840
Everywhere I went, I got great shots.

34
00:01:03,460 --> 00:01:06,940
=Truth Supply Station=

35
00:01:06,980 --> 00:01:08,520
(Case talk over. Time to refuel.)

36
00:01:08,520 --> 00:01:10,080
Come on, let's eat.

37
00:01:11,320 --> 00:01:12,000
You good now?

38
00:01:12,960 --> 00:01:14,200
Yeah, I'm good.

39
00:01:14,200 --> 00:01:14,760
That wasn't scary.

40
00:01:14,980 --> 00:01:15,660
(Bursts out laughing)

41
00:01:15,700 --> 00:01:17,100
(What really happened)

42
00:01:17,140 --> 00:01:18,580
(Proceeding very carefully)

43
00:01:19,980 --> 00:01:22,380
(So scared he turned into a blur)

44
00:01:26,540 --> 00:01:29,860
(OMG, you scared me)

45
00:01:30,440 --> 00:01:32,280
That wasn't scary. It was just acting.

46
00:01:32,280 --> 00:01:34,040
(Terrified)
It was scary.

47
00:01:34,480 --> 00:01:35,840
Once you get through it, it's fine.

48
00:01:35,840 --> 00:01:37,220
(No big deal)

49
00:01:37,440 --> 00:01:38,520
They won't scare us at night, right?

50
00:01:38,520 --> 00:01:39,460
(Scared out of mind)

51
00:01:40,800 --> 00:01:41,560
(Recalling)
The first time...

52
00:01:42,640 --> 00:01:44,200
The first time we played,

53
00:01:44,200 --> 00:01:45,960
I was so scared
that I slept with the lights on.

54
00:01:46,440 --> 00:01:47,800
(Possibly traumatized)
The first one is the scariest.

55
00:01:47,800 --> 00:01:48,960
I don't know why.

56
00:01:48,960 --> 00:01:50,880
I did an escape room in Beijing once.

57
00:01:50,880 --> 00:01:52,360
After I got home,

58
00:01:52,360 --> 00:01:55,240
I rewatched the horror movie

59
00:01:55,240 --> 00:01:55,880
it was based on.

60
00:01:55,880 --> 00:01:57,000
That made me even more scared.

61
00:01:57,000 --> 00:01:58,400
You still watched
a horror movie after that?

62
00:01:58,400 --> 00:01:59,180
(Respect)

63
00:02:00,480 --> 00:02:02,200
You've got guts.

64
00:02:02,200 --> 00:02:03,040
Big mistake.

65
00:02:03,040 --> 00:02:04,480
I couldn't sleep for days afterward.

66
00:02:06,900 --> 00:02:08,180
(Food break unlocked!)

67
00:02:11,080 --> 00:02:12,480
You want the end seat?

68
00:02:14,560 --> 00:02:15,520
(Joined at the hip)
I'll sit with you.

69
00:02:15,520 --> 00:02:17,360
Can I sit with Jin?

70
00:02:17,360 --> 00:02:17,760
Is that okay?

71
00:02:18,160 --> 00:02:18,880
Sure.

72
00:02:18,880 --> 00:02:20,400
(Broccoli superfan)
Perfect. I wanted the broccoli anyway.

73
00:02:20,960 --> 00:02:21,800
I wanted this too.

74
00:02:22,600 --> 00:02:23,800
(Lotus Root & Pork Rib Soup)
Is that bone broth?

75
00:02:25,720 --> 00:02:26,920
I'm starving.

76
00:02:27,040 --> 00:02:28,200
(Waiting eagerly)
Can we...

77
00:02:28,200 --> 00:02:29,000
Can we eat now?

78
00:02:29,000 --> 00:02:30,560
No, we have to wait for Ning.

79
00:02:30,560 --> 00:02:31,560
Gotta wait.

80
00:02:32,120 --> 00:02:32,840
(Snack stash)
Try this.

81
00:02:33,680 --> 00:02:34,080
Um...

82
00:02:38,640 --> 00:02:39,240
Where are the drinks?

83
00:02:39,240 --> 00:02:40,400
They're with me.

84
00:02:40,400 --> 00:02:41,840
Want some Thai tea?

85
00:02:43,480 --> 00:02:44,200
Thai tea?

86
00:02:44,640 --> 00:02:46,360
(Caring sister)
Do you want Thai tea or something else?

87
00:02:46,760 --> 00:02:47,440
What else is there?

88
00:02:48,680 --> 00:02:50,200
Orange juice, coffee, and water.

89
00:02:50,200 --> 00:02:51,040
I'll have water.

90
00:02:51,040 --> 00:02:51,680
Water.

91
00:02:51,680 --> 00:02:53,440
Look at her being all disciplined.

92
00:02:53,440 --> 00:02:55,200
Why'd they give us food?

93
00:02:55,940 --> 00:02:58,060
(Curious)

94
00:02:58,360 --> 00:02:59,800
Because it'll be dark when we're done.

95
00:02:59,800 --> 00:03:01,760
Then it's time

96
00:03:01,760 --> 00:03:02,840
(Horror mode loading)
for the scary part.

97
00:03:04,000 --> 00:03:05,360
You're way too excited.

98
00:03:08,280 --> 00:03:09,760
You just have to step out there.

99
00:03:09,760 --> 00:03:11,440
Once you face it, it's not as bad.

100
00:03:11,440 --> 00:03:12,760
The hardest part is that first step.

101
00:03:12,760 --> 00:03:14,720
Once you take it,

102
00:03:14,720 --> 00:03:15,720
(Ding's advice)
there's no turning back.

103
00:03:15,720 --> 00:03:17,200
Then you just keep going.

104
00:03:18,380 --> 00:03:20,100
(Taking notes)

105
00:03:20,600 --> 00:03:21,040
Exactly.

106
00:03:21,040 --> 00:03:21,660
(Agrees)

107
00:03:21,700 --> 00:03:22,240
(Still traumatized)

108
00:03:22,240 --> 00:03:23,360
She was right there on the ground.

109
00:03:23,360 --> 00:03:24,560
That woman...

110
00:03:24,920 --> 00:03:25,680
The way she moved...

111
00:03:30,120 --> 00:03:30,840
She walked like this.

112
00:03:31,960 --> 00:03:32,600
Yeah, like this.

113
00:03:33,520 --> 00:03:34,680
(Getting sidetracked)
Her back is amazing. I'm jealous.

114
00:03:35,460 --> 00:03:36,500
(Seriously?)

115
00:03:36,580 --> 00:03:37,340
(That's what you noticed?)

116
00:03:37,480 --> 00:03:39,160
She had to be a dancer.

117
00:03:39,440 --> 00:03:42,000
(Someone's hungry)
Jin, can you top mine off?

118
00:03:42,440 --> 00:03:43,480
Have some veggies.

119
00:03:44,460 --> 00:03:45,140
(Yes, Jin)

120
00:03:45,240 --> 00:03:47,080
(Asking the real question)
How did you all get skinny so fast?

121
00:03:48,000 --> 00:03:48,360
Working out.

122
00:03:49,820 --> 00:03:52,140
(Ke Stubborn is here)

123
00:03:54,960 --> 00:03:55,560
Careful.

124
00:03:56,200 --> 00:03:57,320
Is it good?

125
00:03:57,320 --> 00:03:58,880
It's pretty good. Classic milk tea.

126
00:03:58,880 --> 00:04:00,640
It tastes super old-school.

127
00:04:01,240 --> 00:04:02,080
My friend...

128
00:04:03,520 --> 00:04:04,920
How'd that get on my shirt?

129
00:04:06,720 --> 00:04:08,160
It's just water. It should be fine.

130
00:04:08,160 --> 00:04:09,040
Is it water?

131
00:04:09,040 --> 00:04:10,840
Did I spill water on my clothes
while pouring yours?

132
00:04:11,120 --> 00:04:12,320
Where are the drinks?

133
00:04:13,120 --> 00:04:14,400
(Jin to the rescue)
What do you want?

134
00:04:14,400 --> 00:04:15,640
Thai tea, orange juice, or coffee?

135
00:04:15,640 --> 00:04:17,440
I'll take Thai tea.

136
00:04:17,440 --> 00:04:18,840
What's Thai tea?

137
00:04:19,240 --> 00:04:20,200
Thai milk tea.

138
00:04:20,200 --> 00:04:21,240
Thai-style milk tea.

139
00:04:21,240 --> 00:04:21,960
"Thai tea" means...

140
00:04:22,960 --> 00:04:24,960
(Deadpan nonsense)
tea from your great-grandma.

141
00:04:25,020 --> 00:04:26,380
(He cracks himself up)

142
00:04:26,420 --> 00:04:27,780
(Enough already)

143
00:04:28,880 --> 00:04:29,440
(Ning Waver's here)
Sorry.

144
00:04:30,720 --> 00:04:31,280
Sorry.

145
00:04:32,280 --> 00:04:33,160
(Finally, Ning's here)
Come on.

146
00:04:33,160 --> 00:04:33,880
Let's eat.

147
00:04:35,160 --> 00:04:36,000
(Dig in)
Let's eat, Ning.

148
00:04:40,960 --> 00:04:41,640
(Focused on eating)
Eat up.

149
00:04:41,640 --> 00:04:43,160
(Help yourself)
Serve yourself.

150
00:04:43,800 --> 00:04:44,640
(Treating herself)
I want some lotus root.

151
00:04:47,280 --> 00:04:48,920
So today there's no

152
00:04:48,920 --> 00:04:49,560
extra food or anything?

153
00:04:50,320 --> 00:04:51,080
What do you mean, "extra food"?

154
00:04:51,880 --> 00:04:52,800
Jin,

155
00:04:52,800 --> 00:04:53,720
I got three.

156
00:04:55,820 --> 00:04:56,500
(Suddenly serious)

157
00:04:56,520 --> 00:04:58,120
You got three today?

158
00:05:00,060 --> 00:05:01,420
(Completely confused)

159
00:05:03,420 --> 00:05:05,660
(Got you again)

160
00:05:05,680 --> 00:05:07,800
(#Ding spots everything)
Such a beautiful woman

161
00:05:07,800 --> 00:05:09,600
(Fully committed to the bit)
has completely stolen my heart.

162
00:05:09,600 --> 00:05:11,360
Every smile and every glance

163
00:05:11,360 --> 00:05:13,200
is etched into my heart.

164
00:05:13,200 --> 00:05:15,300
(Sneaking around)

165
00:05:15,820 --> 00:05:16,980
(Hidden stamina marker found)

166
00:05:17,740 --> 00:05:20,420
(Hurry, hurry!)

167
00:05:22,840 --> 00:05:23,680
Keep the scene going.

168
00:05:25,080 --> 00:05:26,240
Hold on, let me scan this first.

169
00:05:30,220 --> 00:05:31,460
(Ding Chengxin +100 stamina points)

170
00:05:34,040 --> 00:05:36,720
(Still fully in character)
Or should I put you into that coffin?

171
00:05:36,720 --> 00:05:37,240
Fine!

172
00:05:39,080 --> 00:05:40,720
The young master wants you gone.

173
00:05:49,400 --> 00:05:50,840
The ghost soldiers said it too,

174
00:05:50,840 --> 00:05:52,280
and they said the bun tasted awful.

175
00:05:53,800 --> 00:05:54,800
Witchcraft.

176
00:05:54,800 --> 00:05:55,840
Poison with evil intent.

177
00:05:55,840 --> 00:05:56,680
Evil intent, hidden poison.

178
00:05:56,680 --> 00:05:57,960
Poisoned heart, evil intent.

179
00:05:57,960 --> 00:05:59,880
Harboring evil intentions.

180
00:06:02,240 --> 00:06:03,040
Let me scan this.

181
00:06:05,320 --> 00:06:06,840
It really
is "harboring evil intentions".

182
00:06:06,840 --> 00:06:07,160
Right.

183
00:06:07,160 --> 00:06:08,600
But I don't have that.

184
00:06:08,600 --> 00:06:10,720
My "bun" answer was right.

185
00:06:10,740 --> 00:06:12,140
(Hidden stamina marker found)

186
00:06:12,940 --> 00:06:13,900
(Double-checking)

187
00:06:14,500 --> 00:06:15,740
(Ding Chengxin +100 stamina points)

188
00:06:19,200 --> 00:06:20,360
(Still playing amnesiac)
What's this?

189
00:06:20,360 --> 00:06:22,480
This is your ticket to food.

190
00:06:22,480 --> 00:06:23,160
Meal card.

191
00:06:24,880 --> 00:06:25,640
Oh no!

192
00:06:26,360 --> 00:06:27,280
I totally forgot.

193
00:06:29,120 --> 00:06:30,640
Is it important?

194
00:06:30,640 --> 00:06:32,000
Very. Like, extremely important.

195
00:06:32,760 --> 00:06:33,640
Not important.

196
00:06:33,640 --> 00:06:36,160
It decides your fate.

197
00:06:36,600 --> 00:06:38,080
I just remembered something.

198
00:06:38,620 --> 00:06:40,540
(Hidden stamina marker found)

199
00:06:48,860 --> 00:06:50,020
(Ding Chengxin +100 stamina points)

200
00:06:52,700 --> 00:06:53,700
(Dungeon 3, Case 1: Stamina Summary)

201
00:06:53,700 --> 00:06:54,700
(Liu Yuning, Jin Jing, Zhang Linghe: 0
Zhou Keyu:0, Ding Chengxin: 300)

202
00:06:54,700 --> 00:06:55,700
(Stamina Summary
Zhang Linghe, Zhou Keyu: 0)

203
00:06:55,700 --> 00:06:56,700
(Liu Yuning: 180, Jin Jing: 100,
Ding Chengxin: 500)

204
00:06:56,720 --> 00:06:59,200
For successfully fixing the glitch
in Dungeon 3,

205
00:06:59,200 --> 00:07:00,560
the system is giving you

206
00:07:00,560 --> 00:07:02,880
(It broke in the best possible way)
free food for the rest of Dungeon 3.

207
00:07:02,880 --> 00:07:05,000
(Stamina points carry over)
Eat as much as you want.

208
00:07:05,000 --> 00:07:05,620
(Can be used later)

209
00:07:06,040 --> 00:07:06,880
I'm telling you,

210
00:07:06,880 --> 00:07:08,720
he's the best at finding free food.

211
00:07:09,160 --> 00:07:10,480
Honestly, that's kind of perfect.

212
00:07:10,480 --> 00:07:11,680
At least you did all that scanning

213
00:07:11,680 --> 00:07:12,880
without interrupting us

214
00:07:12,880 --> 00:07:14,120
while we were actually solving the case.

215
00:07:14,120 --> 00:07:15,120
Right.

216
00:07:15,120 --> 00:07:16,240
I did it quietly.

217
00:07:16,240 --> 00:07:18,480
You found them in the dark?

218
00:07:18,480 --> 00:07:19,720
No way. I'm not that brave.

219
00:07:20,240 --> 00:07:22,160
You think I'd walk around in the dark?

220
00:07:22,160 --> 00:07:23,600
There were two by the front desk.

221
00:07:23,600 --> 00:07:25,520
Awesome.

222
00:07:25,520 --> 00:07:26,760
We don't have to pay today.

223
00:07:26,760 --> 00:07:28,360
Then what was I doing all day

224
00:07:29,760 --> 00:07:30,560
(Heartbroken)
for?

225
00:07:32,320 --> 00:07:33,280
You...

226
00:07:33,980 --> 00:07:35,260
(At least you tried)

227
00:07:35,280 --> 00:07:36,160
Save them for next time.

228
00:07:36,160 --> 00:07:36,920
You'll need them later.

229
00:07:37,800 --> 00:07:38,720
Maybe even next season.

230
00:07:38,720 --> 00:07:39,600
Just keep saving them.

231
00:07:39,660 --> 00:07:42,300
(Actually feels a little better)

232
00:07:44,300 --> 00:07:45,420
(He just can't keep a secret)

233
00:07:45,440 --> 00:07:46,720
The system has detected

234
00:07:46,720 --> 00:07:50,120
Ding Pillar gained 300 stamina points.

235
00:07:50,120 --> 00:07:51,960
How many times did Jin Thrifty

236
00:07:51,960 --> 00:07:53,440
gain stamina points in this stage?

237
00:07:54,240 --> 00:07:54,840
Zero.

238
00:07:54,840 --> 00:07:56,580
(Let's not bring up painful memories)

239
00:07:56,600 --> 00:07:57,160
Okay.

240
00:07:57,920 --> 00:07:58,600
So...

241
00:07:59,160 --> 00:08:01,040
Her card was basically a prop.

242
00:08:01,460 --> 00:08:03,380
(Don't say it)

243
00:08:03,920 --> 00:08:04,520
(Poor thing)
Poor Jin.

244
00:08:04,960 --> 00:08:06,160
I even looked for one today.

245
00:08:06,160 --> 00:08:06,960
I couldn't find any.

246
00:08:06,960 --> 00:08:08,160
(Where are my stamina points?)

247
00:08:08,160 --> 00:08:10,040
Ding scanned one right in front of me.

248
00:08:11,880 --> 00:08:12,600
I saw one.

249
00:08:12,600 --> 00:08:13,280
But when I went to scan it,

250
00:08:13,280 --> 00:08:15,000
Ding told me he'd already used it.

251
00:08:15,000 --> 00:08:17,780
(Genius Ding)

252
00:08:18,320 --> 00:08:20,560
Why is everyone so sneaky
about scanning this time?

253
00:08:21,280 --> 00:08:22,800
We didn't want to kill the mood.

254
00:08:22,800 --> 00:08:23,720
You can't just yell, "I found one"!

255
00:08:24,840 --> 00:08:25,960
Exactly.

256
00:08:27,120 --> 00:08:28,080
Scan what?

257
00:08:28,080 --> 00:08:30,520
We all get a meal card.

258
00:08:30,520 --> 00:08:33,960
There are hidden markers

259
00:08:33,960 --> 00:08:35,080
where you can load up points.

260
00:08:35,080 --> 00:08:36,040
You scan your card

261
00:08:36,040 --> 00:08:37,360
and earn 100 points.

262
00:08:37,360 --> 00:08:38,240
The points are basically cash.

263
00:08:39,400 --> 00:08:41,080
So your card has spending money.

264
00:08:41,080 --> 00:08:42,520
Got points? You eat.

265
00:08:42,520 --> 00:08:43,600
No points, and you have to...

266
00:08:44,360 --> 00:08:44,720
Beg.

267
00:08:44,720 --> 00:08:45,240
Ask.

268
00:08:45,840 --> 00:08:46,600
Beg for food.

269
00:08:46,600 --> 00:08:47,280
Beg.

270
00:08:47,280 --> 00:08:48,260
(Cracks up)

271
00:08:48,400 --> 00:08:49,440
It's not begging.

272
00:08:49,800 --> 00:08:51,160
Got points? You eat.

273
00:08:51,160 --> 00:08:52,160
If you don't,

274
00:08:52,160 --> 00:08:54,200
you ask someone else to buy you food.

275
00:08:55,720 --> 00:08:57,000
So just ask? Easy.

276
00:08:57,000 --> 00:08:58,360
(Zero hesitation)
Please.

277
00:08:58,360 --> 00:08:59,040
Feed me.

278
00:08:59,040 --> 00:09:01,560
I'm hungry. Please, feed me.

279
00:09:02,040 --> 00:09:02,880
Even then,

280
00:09:02,880 --> 00:09:04,160
he still might say no.

281
00:09:04,820 --> 00:09:05,520
(Is that true?)

282
00:09:05,520 --> 00:09:08,120
But the Big Bro No. 2 is kind of stingy.

283
00:09:08,680 --> 00:09:09,160
Stingy?

284
00:09:09,880 --> 00:09:10,840
I'm stingy?

285
00:09:11,480 --> 00:09:11,720
Eat.

286
00:09:12,160 --> 00:09:12,680
Eat what?

287
00:09:13,200 --> 00:09:13,520
Yeah, eat.

288
00:09:15,040 --> 00:09:16,080
The Truth Happiness Set.

289
00:09:16,080 --> 00:09:17,320
I'll pay 100. You guys pay 200.

290
00:09:17,320 --> 00:09:19,200
Okay, I'll buy one Truth Hunan Set.

291
00:09:19,200 --> 00:09:20,600
Sure, I'll order a Truth Taste Set.

292
00:09:20,840 --> 00:09:23,640
Is he seriously dragging me right now?

293
00:09:23,640 --> 00:09:25,240
Who bought you food last time?

294
00:09:25,840 --> 00:09:26,760
(Truth revealed)
Relax, I'm kidding.

295
00:09:26,760 --> 00:09:28,160
I like messing with people.

296
00:09:28,820 --> 00:09:31,580
(You're forgiven)

297
00:09:31,960 --> 00:09:33,400
Honestly, Yue handled it pretty well.

298
00:09:33,400 --> 00:09:34,280
She's actually pretty brave.

299
00:09:34,580 --> 00:09:35,580
(Agreed)

300
00:09:36,000 --> 00:09:36,400
I was okay.

301
00:09:37,320 --> 00:09:38,760
I was just thinking...

302
00:09:38,760 --> 00:09:40,280
Imagine if it were...

303
00:09:40,280 --> 00:09:41,960
Like Wen and Qian, for example.

304
00:09:41,960 --> 00:09:43,200
(It was terrifying)
She got so scared she cried.

305
00:09:43,200 --> 00:09:43,920
She really cried.

306
00:09:44,460 --> 00:09:46,300
(Was it that scary?)

307
00:09:47,560 --> 00:09:49,720
No, I think that day was...

308
00:09:49,720 --> 00:09:51,120
No, that day was scarier.

309
00:09:51,400 --> 00:09:51,840
Really?

310
00:09:52,640 --> 00:09:54,120
Because it came out of nowhere.

311
00:09:54,120 --> 00:09:55,160
We were just walking around.

312
00:09:55,160 --> 00:09:57,040
And that day,

313
00:09:57,520 --> 00:09:59,480
we'd been in character for so long.

314
00:10:00,820 --> 00:10:01,660
(Listening closely)

315
00:10:01,680 --> 00:10:03,080
Then nighttime hit,

316
00:10:03,080 --> 00:10:03,960
and boom! It happened.

317
00:10:04,060 --> 00:10:05,340
Ah!

318
00:10:06,440 --> 00:10:08,440
Don't! Please!

319
00:10:12,320 --> 00:10:12,760
Right.

320
00:10:12,760 --> 00:10:13,400
It was so scary.

321
00:10:13,400 --> 00:10:14,280
We'd let our guard down.

322
00:10:14,280 --> 00:10:15,280
Exactly. Our guard was down.

323
00:10:15,340 --> 00:10:17,500
(Doesn't look thrilled)

324
00:10:17,520 --> 00:10:18,680
You know why today was easier?

325
00:10:18,680 --> 00:10:20,520
We knew this was classic horror

326
00:10:20,520 --> 00:10:21,800
and kept talking
about how scary it'd be,

327
00:10:21,800 --> 00:10:22,880
so we were ready for it.

328
00:10:22,880 --> 00:10:25,160
That other time was our first shoot.

329
00:10:25,160 --> 00:10:27,520
We forgot this was even a horror show.

330
00:10:27,520 --> 00:10:29,040
We were just casually walking around,

331
00:10:29,040 --> 00:10:30,120
then the lights went out.

332
00:10:30,120 --> 00:10:31,440
Then someone

333
00:10:31,440 --> 00:10:32,760
started creeping closer and closer.

334
00:10:32,760 --> 00:10:33,800
And the lights kept flickering.

335
00:10:33,820 --> 00:10:36,060
(At least we were prepared today)

336
00:10:36,360 --> 00:10:37,040
How's today's case

337
00:10:37,040 --> 00:10:38,400
going so far?

338
00:10:39,040 --> 00:10:40,080
I've got nothing.

339
00:10:40,080 --> 00:10:41,280
But I think...

340
00:10:41,960 --> 00:10:43,120
Nothing?

341
00:10:43,120 --> 00:10:44,600
No, this move is seriously hard.

342
00:10:44,600 --> 00:10:46,480
My legendary kick...

343
00:10:46,480 --> 00:10:47,760
Isn't it kind of like...

344
00:10:47,760 --> 00:10:49,160
Crippled Kick?

345
00:10:49,160 --> 00:10:50,080
But your legendary kick

346
00:10:50,080 --> 00:10:51,560
actually paid off later.

347
00:10:51,560 --> 00:10:52,520
(All-around Ning)
You used it

348
00:10:52,520 --> 00:10:53,760
in the challenge,
and it won you the round.

349
00:10:54,520 --> 00:10:54,960
A little farther.

350
00:10:55,020 --> 00:10:57,460
(Perfect full split)

351
00:10:57,480 --> 00:10:58,520
That was on purpose.

352
00:10:58,520 --> 00:10:59,520
I really didn't want to do the splits,

353
00:10:59,520 --> 00:11:01,600
but I had to commit to the character.

354
00:11:01,600 --> 00:11:03,800
You're crazy flexible, though.

355
00:11:03,800 --> 00:11:05,440
Usually, tall guys like you

356
00:11:05,440 --> 00:11:06,600
aren't that flexible.

357
00:11:06,600 --> 00:11:09,160
Yeah, my hamstrings are pretty flexible.

358
00:11:09,160 --> 00:11:10,680
I trained in martial arts

359
00:11:11,320 --> 00:11:12,360
as a kid for a while.

360
00:11:12,620 --> 00:11:14,280
(Jealous)

361
00:11:14,280 --> 00:11:15,560
I stretched every day back then.

362
00:11:15,560 --> 00:11:16,680
My muscles

363
00:11:16,680 --> 00:11:17,640
(Another skill never hurts)

364
00:11:17,640 --> 00:11:19,160
got really loose
from all that stretching.

365
00:11:19,780 --> 00:11:21,540
(Meanwhile...)

366
00:11:21,540 --> 00:11:33,940
(#The Food Bros
are quietly destroying the food)

367
00:11:33,940 --> 00:11:36,460
(Still not enough)

368
00:11:37,160 --> 00:11:38,640
What'd you guys do in France?

369
00:11:38,640 --> 00:11:39,760
Eat anything good?

370
00:11:40,240 --> 00:11:41,080
We played a bunch of games.

371
00:11:41,080 --> 00:11:42,600
Was it fun?

372
00:11:42,600 --> 00:11:43,520
Yeah.

373
00:11:43,520 --> 00:11:44,880
Was the travel show fun?

374
00:11:44,880 --> 00:11:45,440
(Answers both)
Yeah.

375
00:11:46,400 --> 00:11:47,120
It was fun.

376
00:11:47,120 --> 00:11:48,000
You went too?

377
00:11:48,880 --> 00:11:49,600
I joined for one episode.

378
00:11:49,960 --> 00:11:51,360
Everywhere I went, I got great shots.

379
00:11:51,360 --> 00:11:52,120
They came out so good.

380
00:11:54,560 --> 00:11:55,240
Really good.

381
00:11:55,240 --> 00:11:56,400
I saw them.

382
00:11:57,040 --> 00:11:57,840
She loved it.

383
00:11:57,840 --> 00:11:58,520
Just sitting in the car.

384
00:11:58,520 --> 00:11:59,720
We were driving around,
and she kept saying

385
00:11:59,720 --> 00:12:01,560
everywhere looked like a photo op.

386
00:12:01,560 --> 00:12:02,920
She wanted pictures everywhere.

387
00:12:03,240 --> 00:12:04,440
(Might as well)
Already there. Must get the shot.

388
00:12:05,080 --> 00:12:06,120
And we went to this little town...

389
00:12:06,120 --> 00:12:07,160
Right, I brought you all

390
00:12:07,160 --> 00:12:08,240
something from there.

391
00:12:08,240 --> 00:12:09,840
There was this pottery village nearby

392
00:12:09,840 --> 00:12:10,640
that sold...

393
00:12:11,760 --> 00:12:13,040
Because France is famous

394
00:12:13,040 --> 00:12:13,760
for lavender.

395
00:12:13,760 --> 00:12:15,440
We bought
some lavender-filled teddy bears.

396
00:12:15,840 --> 00:12:16,960
You went to the south of France?

397
00:12:16,960 --> 00:12:17,880
Yeah, the south of France.

398
00:12:17,880 --> 00:12:18,800
It was beautiful.

399
00:12:18,800 --> 00:12:20,200
The real lavender smells

400
00:12:20,200 --> 00:12:21,120
exactly like the stuff they sell.

401
00:12:21,120 --> 00:12:22,600
I literally crouched by the field
to smell it.

402
00:12:23,120 --> 00:12:24,040
Exactly the same.

403
00:12:24,040 --> 00:12:24,800
Exactly the same?

404
00:12:24,800 --> 00:12:25,480
Yeah, exactly the same.

405
00:12:26,120 --> 00:12:26,880
The exact same smell.

406
00:12:26,880 --> 00:12:28,440
They also had lavender ice cream.

407
00:12:28,440 --> 00:12:29,760
It was weird,
almost like eating a pillow.

408
00:12:31,520 --> 00:12:32,400
(Wait, what?)
Eating a pillow?

409
00:12:32,400 --> 00:12:33,240
For real.

410
00:12:33,240 --> 00:12:33,560
It was...

411
00:12:33,560 --> 00:12:34,200
The second she said that,

412
00:12:34,200 --> 00:12:35,400
I was like, "That's exactly it".

413
00:12:35,400 --> 00:12:35,760
Yeah.

414
00:12:37,080 --> 00:12:37,880
How long were you there?

415
00:12:38,480 --> 00:12:39,600
Twelve days.

416
00:12:40,280 --> 00:12:41,680
So when you were in France,

417
00:12:41,680 --> 00:12:43,360
how did you communicate?

418
00:12:43,720 --> 00:12:45,040
Most of the time,

419
00:12:45,040 --> 00:12:46,880
there was usually someone
who spoke English.

420
00:12:47,300 --> 00:12:48,180
(Learning something new)

421
00:12:48,200 --> 00:12:50,400
Yeah, English gets you by.

422
00:12:50,400 --> 00:12:52,600
But yeah, they mostly speak French.

423
00:12:52,600 --> 00:12:53,760
French is still the main language.

424
00:12:53,780 --> 00:12:55,620
(I see)

425
00:12:56,960 --> 00:12:58,600
Okay, who's the killer today?

426
00:12:58,600 --> 00:13:01,000
Tell us now.
We'll pretend we never heard it.

427
00:13:01,480 --> 00:13:02,400
Come on, just confess.

428
00:13:04,240 --> 00:13:04,880
Just confess?

429
00:13:04,880 --> 00:13:05,280
Exactly.

430
00:13:05,280 --> 00:13:06,120
And we'll pretend we don't know?

431
00:13:13,160 --> 00:13:13,760
Just confess.

432
00:13:14,680 --> 00:13:15,400
Same game again?

433
00:13:15,400 --> 00:13:17,200
Everyone closes their eyes,

434
00:13:17,200 --> 00:13:18,160
and the killer opens their eyes.

435
00:13:18,160 --> 00:13:20,240
Only the detective gets to see it.

436
00:13:20,240 --> 00:13:22,120
Then figures it out from there?

437
00:13:22,120 --> 00:13:22,920
Really?

438
00:13:22,920 --> 00:13:23,480
You've done that before?

439
00:13:23,480 --> 00:13:24,160
Yeah, we have.

440
00:13:24,160 --> 00:13:25,400
And someone
really opened their eyes once.

441
00:13:25,880 --> 00:13:26,480
(Really?)
Someone did?

442
00:13:27,200 --> 00:13:27,720
No.

443
00:13:27,720 --> 00:13:29,080
By then,

444
00:13:29,080 --> 00:13:30,960
we already knew
she wasn't the real killer.

445
00:13:31,360 --> 00:13:33,960
We weren't totally sure then, were we?

446
00:13:34,520 --> 00:13:35,440
No, we were.

447
00:13:36,240 --> 00:13:37,520
But she really did open her eyes.

448
00:13:37,520 --> 00:13:39,160
Right now, honestly...

449
00:13:39,160 --> 00:13:40,560
none of us can tell.

450
00:13:40,580 --> 00:13:41,200
(Difficulty increased)

451
00:13:41,200 --> 00:13:41,800
Yeah, can't tell.

452
00:13:42,700 --> 00:13:43,540
(Good point)

453
00:13:43,540 --> 00:14:25,500
=The Truth (Season 4)=
(Viewing Calendar)

454
00:14:57,220 --> 00:15:01,220
♪Come now, players all,
let the game of reason start♪

455
00:15:01,220 --> 00:15:05,660
♪Unlock each hidden trial,
let courage spark the dark♪

456
00:15:07,680 --> 00:15:11,840
♪Night falls slow, shadows grow,
the sleuth is lost inside the maze♪

457
00:15:11,840 --> 00:15:16,060
♪Figures pass, lanterns sparse,
dark currents drift without a trace♪

458
00:15:16,060 --> 00:15:19,830
♪Wind picks up, footsteps rush,
cold laughter swallowed by the dark♪

459
00:15:19,830 --> 00:15:23,940
♪Truth concealed, the night
stands still, and nothing leaves a mark♪

460
00:15:24,120 --> 00:15:28,240
♪An unsigned letter, coded words,
the solvers gather one by one♪

461
00:15:28,240 --> 00:15:32,350
♪A broken game, illusion reigns,
who's hiding what they've done?♪

462
00:15:32,350 --> 00:15:35,990
♪Hushed voices, nerves on edge,
wrapped in smoke and mirrors still♪

463
00:15:35,990 --> 00:15:38,120
♪The next second, deeper riddles,
or the answer to the kill♪

464
00:15:38,120 --> 00:15:42,070
♪Every piece of truth
has finally come to light♪

465
00:15:42,310 --> 00:15:46,230
♪Unlock the mystery, turn the question,
let's begin tonight♪

466
00:15:46,440 --> 00:15:50,590
♪Side by side, no holding back,
follow every clue to find the truth♪

467
00:15:50,590 --> 00:15:54,150
♪The story blurs like flowers in fog,
let's begin tonight♪

468
00:15:54,410 --> 00:15:59,060
♪Search for the vanished cipher,
trace the proof, and face the sleuth♪
